			</ul>

			<h2>16th AAAC Annual: Fractured Fairytales</h2>
			<p><span class="date">December 8, 2006 – January 19, 2007</span></p>
			<p>Through a review of the Asian American Artists Slide Archive's previous year's submissions, artists are selected by a panel.  This year five artists who reflect a nexus of themes around personal icons - fantasy, dreams, pop culture, identity, and appropriation - were chosen.  In a complex society with multiple contradictory interests at work, the drive to encompass these through creativity is a sustaining mark of these artists’ works. Together they compose a very current part of the contemporary presence of Asia in America. The Archive is open to all visual artists of Asian ancestry and artists who are strongly influenced by Asia. <i>Learn more: <a href="http://artasiamerica.org/documents/3938/55" target="_blank">brochure</a>, <a href="http://artasiamerica.org/documents/1478/55" target="_blank">postcard</a>.</i></p>
